Police say an undisclosed amount of money was stolen when four armed suspects stormed the shopping centre on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN - A social grant payout point at Stellenbosch’s Eikestad Mall has been robbed. Police say an undisclosed amount of money was stolen when four armed suspects stormed the shopping centre on Tuesday. An armed robbery case is under investigation. Western Cape police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said: “Provincial detectives are in pursuit of four armed suspects who robbed a social grant payout point at Eikestad Mall in Stellenbosch.”